[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6756,
        "end_time": 8720,
        "text": "Almost 2000 years ago,"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 8720,
        "end_time": 14447,
        "text": "the Roman philosopher Seneca peered \nat his book through a glass of water."
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 14447,
        "end_time": 18504,
        "text": "Suddenly, the text below was transformed."
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 18504,
        "end_time": 21790,
        "text": "The words magically became clear."
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 21790,
        "end_time": 25041,
        "text": "But it wasn&#39;t until a millennium later\nthat that same principle"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 25041,
        "end_time": 30143,
        "text": "would be used to create \nthe earliest glasses."
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 30143,
        "end_time": 33622,
        "text": "Today, glasses can help millions of people\nwith poor vision"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 33622,
        "end_time": 36778,
        "text": "due to uncorrected refractive errors."
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 36778,
        "end_time": 40987,
        "text": "The key to understanding what that means\nlies with the term refraction,"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 40987,
        "end_time": 43951,
        "text": "the ability of a transparent medium,\nlike glass,"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 43951,
        "end_time": 44980,
        "text": "water,"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 44980,
        "end_time": 49782,
        "text": "or the eye to change the direction\nof light passing through it."
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 49782,
        "end_time": 52320,
        "text": "The eye has two main refractive surfaces:"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 52320,
        "end_time": 54800,
        "text": "the cornea and the lens."
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 54800,
        "end_time": 57379,
        "text": "Ideally, these surfaces work together"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 57379,
        "end_time": 62137,
        "text": "to refract light in a way that accurately\nfocuses light onto the retina,"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 62137,
        "end_time": 65749,
        "text": "the layer of light-sensitive tissue\nat the back of the eye"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 65749,
        "end_time": 68903,
        "text": "that works with the brain\nto give rise to vision."
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 68903,
        "end_time": 71442,
        "text": "But many people develop refractive errors,"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 71442,
        "end_time": 74213,
        "text": "either during childhood \nas their eyes are growing,"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 74213,
        "end_time": 77402,
        "text": "or in later life as their eyes age."
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 77402,
        "end_time": 79527,
        "text": "Imperfections in the cornea and lens"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 79527,
        "end_time": 84380,
        "text": "cause refracted light to be focused\nin front of or behind the retina,"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 84380,
        "end_time": 87377,
        "text": "making images appear blurry."
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 87377,
        "end_time": 89888,
        "text": "People with refractive errors\ncan still see color,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 89888,
        "end_time": 90946,
        "text": "movement,"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 90946,
        "end_time": 92072,
        "text": "and light,"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 92072,
        "end_time": 95560,
        "text": "but the details of what they&#39;re looking at\nare out of focus."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 95560,
        "end_time": 98840,
        "text": "People experience refractive \nerrors in different ways,"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 98840,
        "end_time": 101320,
        "text": "owing to differences in their eyes."
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 101320,
        "end_time": 103666,
        "text": "In some, light refracts too much,"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 103666,
        "end_time": 105980,
        "text": "and in others, too little."
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 105980,
        "end_time": 109461,
        "text": "Eyes with a focal point \nin front of the retina are called myopic,"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 109461,
        "end_time": 111131,
        "text": "or short-sighted."
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 111131,
        "end_time": 113066,
        "text": "They can see close objects clearly,"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 113066,
        "end_time": 116059,
        "text": "but those far away are out of focus."
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 116059,
        "end_time": 118345,
        "text": "But when the focus point \nis behind the retina,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 118345,
        "end_time": 121627,
        "text": "people are hyperopic,\nor long-sighted."
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 121627,
        "end_time": 124870,
        "text": "For them, objects close up\nare unfocused,"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 124870,
        "end_time": 127907,
        "text": "but distant objects are crystal clear."
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 127907,
        "end_time": 131859,
        "text": "Finally, some people have a cornea\nwith a non-spherical shape"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 131859,
        "end_time": 133790,
        "text": "that causes astigmatism,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 133790,
        "end_time": 138040,
        "text": "a form of out-of-focus vision\nthat makes all objects seem blurred,"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 138040,
        "end_time": 140356,
        "text": "whether close or far."
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 140356,
        "end_time": 143224,
        "text": "As we age, our eyes face new challenges."
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 143224,
        "end_time": 146412,
        "text": "When we&#39;re young, the lens of the eye\nis flexible"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 146412,
        "end_time": 149789,
        "text": "and can change shape to bring\nimages into focus,"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 149789,
        "end_time": 151981,
        "text": "something called accommodation."
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 151981,
        "end_time": 157131,
        "text": "This keeps objects in focus when we\nshift our gaze from far to near."
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 157131,
        "end_time": 160444,
        "text": "But as we get older, the lens becomes\nless flexible,"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 160444,
        "end_time": 164313,
        "text": "and can&#39;t change shape when we want\nto look at near objects."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 164313,
        "end_time": 166404,
        "text": "This is called presbyopia,"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 166404,
        "end_time": 171040,
        "text": "and it affects adults starting\naround the age of 40 years."
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 171040,
        "end_time": 171849,
        "text": "Myopia,"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 171849,
        "end_time": 172776,
        "text": "hyperopia,"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 172776,
        "end_time": 173834,
        "text": "astigmatism,"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 173834,
        "end_time": 175475,
        "text": "and presbyopia."
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 175475,
        "end_time": 177926,
        "text": "Each of these is a refractive error."
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 177926,
        "end_time": 181757,
        "text": "Nowadays we can fix them all with glasses\nor contact lenses,"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 181757,
        "end_time": 187200,
        "text": "which work by refocusing light\nso it strikes the retina precisely."
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 187200,
        "end_time": 189769,
        "text": "It&#39;s even possible to correct vision\nwith surgery"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 189769,
        "end_time": 193086,
        "text": "using lasers that change the shape\nof the cornea"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 193086,
        "end_time": 195656,
        "text": "and alter its refractive properties."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 195656,
        "end_time": 197913,
        "text": "But glasses remain the most popular."
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 197913,
        "end_time": 199880,
        "text": "By using carefully crafted lenses"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 199880,
        "end_time": 203257,
        "text": "to steer light to exactly \nthe right spot on the retina,"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 203257,
        "end_time": 207060,
        "text": "a person&#39;s clear vision can be restored."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 207060,
        "end_time": 209635,
        "text": "We&#39;ve come a long way \nsince Seneca&#39;s discovery"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 209635,
        "end_time": 212178,
        "text": "and the crude glasses of yesteryear."
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 212178,
        "end_time": 216324,
        "text": "In 1727, a British optician named\nEdward Scarlett"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 216324,
        "end_time": 219132,
        "text": "developed the modern style of glasses"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 219132,
        "end_time": 222697,
        "text": "which are kept in place with arms\nwhich hook over each ear."
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 222697,
        "end_time": 226046,
        "text": "Today&#39;s glasses take their inspiration\nfrom that design,"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 226046,
        "end_time": 229753,
        "text": "but they&#39;re also much more precise\nand personal."
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 229753,
        "end_time": 235061,
        "text": "Each pair is tailored for an individual\nto bring out their unique powers of sight."
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 235061,
        "end_time": 240598,
        "text": "So if you&#39;re one of the 500 million people\nwith a problem with close or far vision,"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 240598,
        "end_time": 241883,
        "text": "or both,"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 241883,
        "end_time": 245589,
        "text": "there&#39;s a pair of glasses out there\nwaiting to reveal a whole new world"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 245589,
        "end_time": 247663,
        "text": "that&#39;s hiding in plain view."
    }
]